image.altText: Titans and Knights

props.synopsis: A blisteringly hot day in Sydney will provide the backdrop to rugby league's finales, with Newcastle and Gold Coast facing off in the NRLW grand final before the Panthers and Broncos take the field tonight. Follow live.

title.children: Knights and Titans kick off NRLW grand final in searing Sydney heat

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Hannah Southwell is pinged for a hair-pull on Georgia Hale and Zara Canfield slots the penalty goal from right in front. I don't think this was the start anyone expected. It's been all Gold Coast all the time so far.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 21' The Titans push the lead to 8-0

children.content: Hannah Southwell is pinged for a hair-pull on Georgia Hale and Zara Canfield slots the penalty goal from right in front.
I don't think this was the start anyone expected. It's been all Gold Coast all the time so far.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's former Dragon and Bronco Jaime Chapman who crosses first, charging over from an inside ball from Lauren Brown. Chapman is rapid, powerful and skilled, playing everywhere across the back five and was just impossible to stop there. The conversion from Zara Canfield makes it 6-0 to the Titans.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: The Titans are on the board!

children.content: It's former Dragon and Bronco Jaime Chapman who crosses first, charging over from an inside ball from Lauren Brown.
Chapman is rapid, powerful and skilled, playing everywhere across the back five and was just impossible to stop there.
The conversion from Zara Canfield makes it 6-0 to the Titans.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Titans halfback Lauren Brown is flattened by Laishon Albert-Jones after she kicked it down Tamika Upton's throat. No penalty from Belinda Sharpe. A sign of things to come.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 1' And we're off in the NRLW grand final!

children.content: Titans halfback Lauren Brown is flattened by Laishon Albert-Jones after she kicked it down Tamika Upton's throat. No penalty from Belinda Sharpe. A sign of things to come.
